				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Specifically, to convert PAL video captured at 13.5 MHz to square pixels, you need to crop it to 703x576 and then stretch it to 768x576. (For NTSC, crop to 704x480 then shrink to 640x480.) The 720 pixels include a small amount of signal before (to the left of) and after (to the right of) the 4:3 frame, the &quot;nominal analog blanking&quot;, to let the signal be recentered later for playback.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

