					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Of course here no negative values at RGB output to the tube. Because the last stage with DC path. And at this stage does secondary recover black level right before x-Y signals meets with Y. Before this all paths separated with capacitors, so they have negative signals, like any other amplifiers does. <a href="http://jpegshare.net/images/c9/d0/c9d01726cdbd92902ac0b2e884f99074.png" class="postlink">Sample color module with diagrams from 8 color bars picture.</a> Like <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SMPTE_color_bars" class="postlink">SMPTE bars</a> but with black one.</div>

